  "lifecycle_summary": "Service.Run polls the Postgres projector queue for ScopeGenerationWork claims. For each claim it loads all facts for the scope generation via FactStore.LoadFacts, then calls Runtime.Project which builds a CanonicalMaterialization and content.Materialization from the facts, writes canonical nodes through CanonicalWriter.Write, writes content rows through content.Writer.Write, publishes graph_projection_phase_state rows via PhasePublisher, and enqueues ReducerIntents for shared-domain follow-up via ReducerIntentWriter.Enqueue. On success WorkSink.Ack advances the queue row; on failure WorkSink.Fail records the classified failure. A large-generation semaphore (FactCounter + largeSem channel) bounds how many high-fact-count repositories project concurrently.",
  "entry_points": [
    {"name": "Service.Run", "file": "service.go", "line": 94, "role": "main poll loop — claim, load, project, ack or fail"},
    {"name": "Runtime.Project", "file": "runtime.go", "line": 89, "role": "one projection pass — build, canonical write, content write, intent enqueue"}
  ]
